      "observed_in": "Floors 2 and 15, Act 1 (fought twice, HP varied 38-40 across instances, 40 used here) -- turn 1 always a pure debuff (applies a 'Shrink' effect reducing the player's outgoing damage by 30% while the beetle lives; the real percentage is 30%, but v1 simplifies this to 1 stack of the same standard 25% Weak used everywhere else in the simulator, documented approximation). Attack sequence 7 then 13 was observed directly; no Strength buff was visible so the jump to 13 is left as an explicit fixed second value rather than invented via a buff mechanic we didn't see. Cycle repeats the 13-damage attack after round 3 (not independently confirmed beyond round 3).",
      "approximate": true
